class_notes:
"Twentieth-Century Caribbean Literature"  In this course, we will focus on some selected literary texts that were written before, during, and after the wave of independence movements that swept the English-speaking Caribbean in the decades following World War II. We will read novels, plays, poetry, and nonfiction by George Lamming, Sam Selvon, V.S. Naipaul, Jean Rhys, Louise Bennett, Derek Walcott, and Jamaica Kincaid, addressing issues of colonialism, race, class, gender, migration, diaspora, language, and dialect.


TEXTS:
George Lamming, In the Castle of My Skin (Ann Arbor Paperbacks, 1991), ISBN 9780472064687
Sam Selvon, The Lonely Londoners (Penguin Modern Classics, 2006), ISBN 9780141188416
V.S. Naipaul, A House for Mr. Biswas (Vintage International, 2001), ISBN 9780375707162
Jean Rhys, Wide Sargasso Sea (W.W. Norton and Company, 2016), ISBN 9780393352566
Louise Bennett, Jamaica Labrish (Sangster's Book Stores, 1966), ISBN n/a
Derek Walcott, Dream on Monkey Mountain and Other Plays (Farrar, Straus and Giroux, 1971), ISBN 9780374508609
Jamaica Kincaid, A Small Place (Farrar, Straus and Giroux, 2000), ISBN 9780374527075


PARTICULARS:
